data.title: Francis IV, Duke of Modena
data.text:
Francis IV, Duke of Modena (Francesco Giuseppe Carlo Ambrogio Stanislao; 6 October 1779 – 21 January 1846) was Duke of Modena, Reggio, and Mirandola (from 1815), Duke of Massa and Prince of Carrara (from 1829) Archduke of Austria-Este, Royal Prince of Hungary and Bohemia.

Issue[edit]

Archduchess Maria Theresa of Austria-Este (14 July 1817 - 25 March 1886) married Henri d'Artois, Count of Chambord but had no issue.

Francis V, Duke of Modena (1 June 1819 – 20 November 1875) married Princess Adelgunde of Bavaria but had no surviving issue.

Archduke Ferdinand Karl of Austria-Este (20 July 1821 – 15 December 1849) married Archduchess Elisabeth Franziska of Austria and had issue.

Archduchess Maria Beatrix of Austria-Este 13 February 1824 – 18 March 1906) married Infante Juan, Count of Montizón and had issue.

Titles and styles[edit]

6 October 1779 – 24 December 1806 His Royal Highness Archduke Francis of Austria-Este.

24 December 1806 – 14 July 1814 His Royal Highness The Archduke of Austria-Este.

14 July 1814 – 21 January 1846 His Royal Highness The Duke o Modena, Archduke of Austria-Este.
